d with security team to implement zero-trust network policies and automated TLS certificate rotation.\nJunior Systems Administrator  --  Rackspace Technology\nSan Antonio, TX  |  Aug 2016 -- May 2018----\nAdministered 150+ Linux servers (CentOS, Ubuntu) in a managed hosting environment, maintaining 99.9% uptime.\nWrote Bash and Python scripts to automate routine server provisioning, configuration, and backup tasks.\nAssisted migration of legacy workloads to AWS EC2 and S3, reducing hosting costs by 40%.\nParticipated in on-call rotation and resolved 500+ support tickets with consistent SLA adherence	\N	open	t	2026-05-04 09:26:26.436242	2026-06-20 10:33:18.749353
1	DevOps Engineer	Engineering	Full-time	Mid-level	On-site	\N	ai_generated	## About the Role\nWe are a fast-growing technology company seeking a skilled DevOps Engineer to join our Engineering department. In this mid-level role, you will be responsible for designing, implementing, and maintaining robust infrastructure and automation solutions that support our scalable application stack. You will collaborate closely with development and operations teams to ensure seamless deployment pipelines, high availability, and efficient resource utilization. This position is critical to our mission of delivering reliable, secure, and high-performance software to our customers.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n- Design, implement, and maintain CI/CD pipelines using tools such as Jenkins, GitLab CI, or GitHub Actions to automate testing and deployment processes.\n- Manage and optimize cloud infrastructure (AWS, Azure, or GCP) to ensure scalability, security, and cost-efficiency for production environments.\n- Monitor system performance and application health using tools like Prometheus, Grafana, or Datadog, and proactively address issues to maintain high availability.\n- Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define and enforce infrastructure as code (IaC) practices, ensuring consistency and reproducibility across development and production.\n- Perform capacity planning, resource allocation, and cost optimization for cloud environments to support business growth while maintaining performance standards.\n- Establish and maintain robust incident response protocols, including root cause analysis and post-mortem documentation to improve system resilience.\n\nRequirements\n- Proven experience as a DevOps Engineer with a focus on cloud infrastructure (AWS, Azure, or GCP) and CI/CD pipeline implementation.\n- Strong understanding of containerization technologies (Docker, Kubernetes) and experience deploying applications in containerized environments.\n- Demonstrated proficiency in scripting languages (Python, Bash, or PowerShell) for automation and infrastructure management.\n- Experience with version control systems (Git) and infrastructure as code (IaC) tools such as Terraform, Ansible, or CloudFormation.\n- Solid knowledge of networking concepts, security best practices, and compliance requirements for production systems.\n- Ability to work independently and in a collaborative team environment, with strong communication skills to bridge development and operations.\n\nNice to Have\n- Experience with serverless computing platforms (AWS Lambda, Azure Functions) and event-driven architectures.\n- Familiarity with monitoring and alerting systems beyond basic tools (e.g., ELK stack, Splunk) for comprehensive observability.\n- Knowledge of database management and optimization for both relational and NoSQL databases in production environments.\n\nWhat We Offer\n- Competitive salary and performance-based bonuses to reflect your contributions and growth.\n- Comprehensive health insurance, dental, and vision benefits, as well as 401(k) matching.\n- Opportunities for professional development, including access to industry conferences, training programs, and mentorship from senior engineers.	\N	open	t	2026-04-27 09:40:21.391467	2026-06-20 10:33:21.963241
2	Mechanical Engineer	Engineering	Full-time	Junior	On-site	\N	manual	Job Title: Junior Mechanical Design Engineer\n\nLocation: Beirut, Lebanon\nType: Full-time\n\nJob Description:\n\nWe are seeking a motivated Junior Mechanical Design Engineer to join our engineering team. The ideal candidate will support mechanical design, drafting, and testing activities, working closely with senior engineers on real-world projects.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\nDevelop and modify 2D/3D mechanical designs using CAD software\nPrepare detailed engineering drawings and technical documentation\nAssist in design reviews, revisions, and configuration updates\nPerform basic engineering calculations and support simulations\nSupport prototyping, testing, and validation of mechanical systems\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure design feasibility and quality\nMaintain accurate documentation for manufacturing and suppliers\nRequirements:\nBachelor’s degree in Mechanical Engineering (or final-year student)\nProficiency in CAD tools (AutoCAD, Creo, or similar)\nBasic knowledge of mechanical design principles and engineering analysis\nFamiliarity with MATLAB or similar tools is a plus\nStrong problem-solving and analytical skills\nGood communication and teamwork abilities\nAttention to detail and ability to manage multiple tasks\nPreferred Qualifications (Nice to Have):\nInternship or part-time experience in mechanical design or diagnostics\nExposure to testing, prototyping, or manufacturing processes\nKnowledge of simulation tools (FEA/CFD)\nInterest in automotive or aerospace engineering\nWhat We Offer:\nHands-on experience on real engineering projects\nMentorship from experienced engineers\nOpportunity for growth and skill development\nCollaborative and dynamic work environment	\N	open	t	2026-04-27 11:34:54.205143	2026-06-20 10:33:24.088784
4	Senior HR Business Partner	Human Resources	Full-time	Senior	Hybrid	ceo@diyarme.com	manual	## About the Role\nDiyar is looking for a Senior HR Business Partner to serve as a strategic advisor to our Engineering and Operations divisions. You will drive talent strategy, lead organizational change initiatives, and ensure our people practices align with business objectives.\n\n## Key Responsibilities\n- Partner with senior leaders to develop and execute HR strategies\n- Lead full-cycle recruitment for senior and specialist roles\n- Design performance management frameworks\n- Drive employee engagement programs and culture initiatives\n- Advise on complex employee relations matters\n\n## Requirements\n- 6+ years of HR experience, at least 3 in an HRBP or senior HR role\n- Knowledge of Kuwait Labour Law and GCC employment regulations\n- Experience with HRIS systems (SAP SuccessFactors preferred)\n- Bachelor degree in HR, Business Administration, or related field\n- Arabic and English fluency required	\N	open	t	2026-06-09 19:19:49.167618	2026-06-20 10:33:18.227061
47	Marketing Intern	Marketing	Internship	Junior	Hybrid	\N	ai_generated	## About the Role\nDiyar United Company is seeking a passionate and detail-oriented Marketing Intern to contribute to our dynamic marketing initiatives. This role offers hands-on experience in developing and executing marketing strategies while collaborating with cross-functional teams. The intern will play a key role in supporting our growth and helping shape the company's brand presence in the competitive market.\n\n## Key Responsibilities\n- Develop and implement social media content calendars for multiple platforms to increase engagement and brand visibility\n- Conduct market research to identify target audience trends and opportunities for marketing campaigns\n- Assist in creating and managing email marketing campaigns to drive lead generation and customer retention\n- Analyze campaign performance metrics using tools like Google Analytics and social media insights to optimize strategies\n- Collaborate with the marketing team to brainstorm and execute promotional events and community engagement activities\n- Support the production of marketing materials such as brochures, flyers, and digital assets for client outreach\n- Track and report on key performance indicators (KPIs) to ensure alignment with marketing goals\n\n## Requirements\n- Bachelor’s degree in Marketing, Business, or a related field with a strong academic focus\n- Proficiency in basic marketing tools such as Google Analytics, Canva, and Microsoft Office\n- Demonstrated ability to work independently and meet deadlines in a fast-paced environment\n- Strong understanding of digital marketing principles and social media platforms\n- Experience with data analysis and the ability to translate insights into actionable strategies\n- Excellent communication and interpersonal skills with the ability to collaborate effectively\n- Familiarity with content creation and storytelling techniques for digital and traditional media\n\n## Nice to Have\n- Experience with SEO and content optimization for websites\n- Knowledge of CRM systems like Salesforce or HubSpot\n- Experience in event planning or coordination\n- Understanding of local market dynamics and consumer behavior in the target region\n\n## What We Offer\n- Stipend of $1,500 for the internship period\n- Opportunity to work on real-world marketing projects with a growing company\n- Flexible hybrid work schedule with remote options for certain tasks\n- Professional development opportunities including workshops and mentorship from experienced marketing professionals	\N	open	t	2026-06-25 10:00:33.390962	2026-06-25 10:00:33.390962
