1	1	Nadia Haddad	nadia.haddad@outlook.com	Nadia Haddad  Systems Administrator / Junior DevOps Engineer  nadia.haddad@outlook.com | +961 71 234 567 | linkedin.com/in/nadiahaddad  PROFESSIONAL SUMMARY  Motivated IT professional with 3 years of experience in systems administration and emerging DevOps practices. Comfortable   with   Linux   server   management,   Docker   containerization,   and   basic   AWS   cloud   services.   Currently expanding skills in infrastructure automation and CI/CD tooling. A reliable team player who thrives in fast-paced environments and is eager to transition fully into a DevOps engineering role.  TECHNICAL SKILLS  Cloud Platforms:   AWS (EC2, S3, RDS, basic IAM), some exposure to Azure  Containers:   Docker, Docker Compose (learning Kubernetes basics)  CI/CD:   Jenkins (basic pipeline configuration), GitHub Actions (beginner)  Scripting:   Bash scripting, basic Python automation scripts  Configuration Mgmt:   Basic Ansible playbooks, some shell-based config scripts  Monitoring:   Nagios, basic Grafana dashboards, CloudWatch  Operating Systems:   Linux (Ubuntu, CentOS), Windows Server 2016/2019  Networking:   TCP/IP, DNS, DHCP, basic firewall configuration, VPN setup  WORK EXPERIENCE  Systems Administrator / Junior DevOps -- Cedar Technologies  Beirut, Lebanon | Sep 2023 -- Present  -   Manage and maintain 40+ Linux and Windows servers for a mid-size software company with 120 employees. -   Containerized 5 internal applications using Docker and Docker Compose, reducing environment setup time from hours to minutes. -   Set up basic Jenkins pipelines for automated builds and deployments of 3 microservices. -   Migrated on-premise file storage to AWS S3, implementing lifecycle policies that reduced storage costs by 25%. -   Monitor server health using Nagios and custom Bash alerting scripts, maintaining 99.5% uptime.  IT Support Specialist -- MedNet Solutions  Beirut, Lebanon | Jun 2021 -- Aug 2023  -   Provided Tier 2 technical support for