1	Mid-Level DevOps	1	## About the Role\nWe are a fast-growing technology company seeking a skilled DevOps Engineer to join our Engineering department. In this mid-level role, you will be responsible for designing, implementing, and maintaining robust infrastructure and automation solutions that support our scalable application stack. You will collaborate closely with development and operations teams to ensure seamless deployment pipelines, high availability, and efficient resource utilization. This position is critical to our mission of delivering reliable, secure, and high-performance software to our customers.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n- Design, implement, and maintain CI/CD pipelines using tools such as Jenkins, GitLab CI, or GitHub Actions to automate testing and deployment processes.\n- Manage and optimize cloud infrastructure (AWS, Azure, or GCP) to ensure scalability, security, and cost-efficiency for production environments.\n- Monitor system performance and application health using tools like Prometheus, Grafana, or Datadog, and proactively address issues to maintain high availability.\n- Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define and enforce infrastructure as code (IaC) practices, ensuring consistency and reproducibility across development and production.\n- Perform capacity planning, resource allocation, and cost optimization for cloud environments to support business growth while maintaining performance standards.\n- Establish and maintain robust incident response protocols, including root cause analysis and post-mortem documentation to improve system resilience.\n\nRequirements\n- Proven experience as a DevOps Engineer with a focus on cloud infrastructure (AWS, Azure, or GCP) and CI/CD pipeline implementation.\n- Strong understanding of containerization technologies (Docker, Kubernetes) and experience deploying applications in containerized environments.\n- Demonstrated proficiency in scripting languages (Python, Bash, or PowerShell) for automation and infrastructure management.\n- Experience with version control systems (Git) and infrastructure as code (IaC) tools such as Terraform, Ansible, or CloudFormation.\n- Solid knowledge of networking concepts, security best practices, and compliance requirements for production systems.\n- Ability to work independently and in a collaborative team environment, with strong communication skills to bridge development and operations.\n\nNice to Have\n- Experience with serverless computing platforms (AWS Lambda, Azure Functions) and event-driven architectures.\n- Familiarity with monitoring and alerting systems beyond basic tools (e.g., ELK stack, Splunk) for comprehensive observability.\n- Knowledge of database management and optimization for both relational and NoSQL databases in production environments.\n\nWhat We Offer\n- Competitive salary and performance-based bonuses to reflect your contributions and growth.\n- Comprehensive health insurance, dental, and vision benefits, as well as 401(k) matching.\n- Opportunities for professional development, including access to industry conferences, training programs, and mentorship from senior engineers.	40	35	25	2026-04-27 09:46:49.118446	[{"text": "5+ years of experience", "weight": 1, "required": true}]
